description: Put General “Fireball” Flynn at the head of a squad of U.S. Marines and they’d charge a Jap force ten times their size. Flynn knew only one way to fight Japs – straight into them every time. So stranded, alone on a Pacific island, with a force of Japs hunting him down, Flynn drew his pistol for a wild, war-whooping charge. Then he looked round, his jaw dropped, his shoulders sagged. This time there wouldn’t be a squad of U.S. Marines behind him.
name: Operation Castaway

description: Cecil Fowler didn't think that his first name was one a policeman could be proud of - especially a Military Policeman. "Cecil" didn't suggest the courage and cool nerve a Redcap needed, yet Cecil's duties were at the front line... where the red cap cover of the Military Police was usually to be found at the most strategic points - where the enemy fire was thickest!
name: Fighting Redcap

description:
During the Second World War, Britain and the US sent vast quantities of war material to Russia to help in the struggle with Nazi Germany.

But this is the story of how some Russian tanks got lost and went the other way, ending up the hands of the British. In the North African desert.

And how the Germans came to wish they hadn't!
name: The Lost Tanks

description:
How does an ex-Confederate Army infantryman, a Johnny Reb, come to be leading a cavalry charge in Argentina with Mapuche Indian allies at either side of him?

It's a long story...
name: Rebel Army

description:
They didn't like each other, Frankie Speed and Bob Bracewell. Bob reckoned Frankie was a ""flash harry"", while Frankie rated Bob as a ""plodding no-hoper."" Even when they both became Commandos, they'd have loved to spend the war trying to outdo one another.

But fate had something else in store for them. Something that involved a diehard Nazi fanatic and a blood red battle in which they'd have to work together if they were to stand any chance of winning.
name: Blood Red Battle

description:
Sergeant Mike Wagner and Private Steve Jackson were US Military Policemen during the Korean War. Nicknamed ""snowdrops"" - on account of their distinctive white helmets - MPs were unpopular with the regular soldiers they had to keep in line but they were the law.

Then, while investigating an assault on an American officer, Steve and Mike discovered that some men were a law unto themselves...
name: Law of the Battlefield

description: As night descended on the mountains of Transylvania the local peasants fearfully locked their doors and barred their windows. And it wasn't the occupying Germans they were trying to keep out, but something far more terrible - for this was a land of legend, superstition... and werewolves!
name: Beware the Werewolf!

description:
It should have been a proud day for Paul Kent when he took charge of HMS Kelvington. It was the command he had dreamed of.

But now the dream was a nightmare, for he had inherited a mutinous crew, a second-in-command he couldn't rely on, and a ship with a reputation for flunking in action. All in all a ship of shame.
name: Ship of Shame

description:
For every man that fought there, the Eastern Front was a living nightmare, a place of fear and horror where the cruel winters could kill just as effectively as an enemy bullet.

For Hans Mayer it was a chilling change from his time in the French Foreign Legion, fighting under a hot sun against ill-armed enemy tribesmen. But the Legion had betrayed him, handed him over to the Nazis. Now he was an outcast - the Wehrmacht, not the Legion, was his home.
name: Outcast!

description:
Movie star Jack Gallacher's films were an inspiration to millions during the Second World War. He was always the likeable, tough-guy hero.

However, when his aircraft crash-landed on a Japanese-held island in the Pacific Theatre, this legend of the silver screen had to fight for real. To ensure that he and his younger brother survived, Jack knew he had to be more than just a Hollywood hero.
name: Hollywood Hero

description:
The Fieseler Fi156 Storch, or Stork, had to be the unlikeliest military aircraft ever. With its big glazed cockpit and long dangling undercarriage legs it looked more like an overgrown insect than a warplane.

Captain Gavin Selby knew all about the Stork's qualities. The tough paratrooper had run up against them more than once. He was in no doubt that the Storks could fight.

What he didn't know was that he's end up fighting, not against them, but with them.
name: The Fighting Storks

description:
The old saying goes, "You can't fit a square peg in a round hole."

Early in the Second World War, though, the British Army tried to do it. And guess what? They found that the old saying was right all along.
name: The Square Pegs

description:
Squadron Leader Jimmy Newman flew his Westland Lysander on very dicey special ops, landing Secret Service agents in enemy territory.

Then he got shot down over occupied France and found himself with a handful of antique aircraft at his disposal. Pretty soon he was helping the resistance thwart the progress of a massive convoy of mighty Waffen SS armour.

But they couldn't do it on their own, they had to get word back to Britain. It was a mission for Jimmy's private air force.
name: Jimmy's Private Air Force

description:
As gunfire rent the air, Jimmy Milligan realised too late that these American MPs were actually SS infiltrators in disguise. His men were dead before they hit the ground, and Jimmy himself was struck in the legs.

Then, with grim intent, the German officer moved towards him, raising his gun slowly, murder in his eyes...
name: Finger On The Trigger

description:
It was an important mission, no doubt about that, but special investigator Anton Brunner still couldn't figure out why anyone would actually try to kill him to stop his enquiries. Yet that's exactly what was happening.

In fact, there had already been four unsuccessful attempts on his life - and this time there was no way out!
name: Operation Shadow

description: The jungle was a dangerous place in 1943. Here a man had to trust his life to a friend, for the enemy dealt solely in death. Sergeant Bill Simes knew this but he wasn't sure if Lieutenant Simon Langley would live long enough to learn, as British, Japs and guerrillas played a deadly game of hide-and-seek in the hot and steamy no-man's-land between Burma and China.
name: Jungle Guns

description:
Meet Conrad Scheller of the Wehrmacht. A lot of folk were keen to have a chat with him... his own people, the British, the Russians.

Make no mistake, he was in great demand.

So far he had fought a very tough war, and it looked as if it was going to get a whole lot tougher...
name: Snatch Squad

description:
It was a well thought-out scheme from a junior Intelligence officer. Mislead German High Command with a map showing the wrong site for the Allied invasion of Europe. That would make sure the Panzer Armies were miles from the vital battleground. The snag was how to go about it.

As it turned out, getting the map into German hands was surprisingly easy. The difficult part was keeping it there!
name: The Map

description:
It's Summer 2008 and young friends Will Knox and Juro Tamura are on an adrenaline-filled extreme sports holiday in Hokkaido, Japan.

However, among activities like martial arts, bungee-jumping and white-water rafting, the lads find themselves embroiled in a dangerous mystery involving stolen information, kidnapped civilians and ruthless North Korean commandos. Not to mention the violent tropical hurricane on the way...

How much more of a nightmare could this holiday possibly become?
name: Nightmare Holiday

description:
Some called it "Jug", some "Razorback". Others nicknamed it "T-Bolt."

No matter what you called the P-47 Thunderbolt, you knew its battery of machine guns and rockets packed a killing punch.

So you certainly didn't want to be in the way of the strike of the thunderbolt.
name: Strike of the Thunderbolt
